{
  "texts": [
    "These results led us to make some considerations: most importantly, that it is surprising to see that ChatGPT performed better in scenarios reporting diseases with relatively low prevalence given ChatGPT's mode of (pre)-training on a vast amount of text data from the internet.",
    "However, in our qualitative analysis, we did not find evidence of similar published cases.",
    "As previously mentioned, prompting strategy had the lowest impact on output rating.",
    "The fact that ChatGPT performed slightly better in clinico-pathological questions with five differential diagnoses to choose from could suggest that doing so narrows the range of diagnostic hypotheses to which ChatGPT must associate the clinico-pathological presentation of the scenario in order to provide the statistically most probable diagnosis.",
    "Indeed, in pathology it is not uncommon for different pathologies to present with similar clinical manifestations and overlapping histological features."
  ]
}